race.comment: JEANS (2) is back from a break of five months. Raced twice in his maiden campaign and wasn't far away on either occasion including the last run when third over 1000m at Sunshine Coast. Tricky draw to overcome but can open the winning account. REIGN OF DAME (8) was always well out of her ground when 6 lengths from the winner in sixth over 1000m at Eagle Farm last start, a less impressive effort than her fourth on debut at this track the run before. Has the class to figure prominently. KING OF VALHALLA (11) resuming from a lay-off. Looking very sharp in training including a win his most recent trial at Gold Coast. Raced just once last campaign and finished fifth at Gold Coast over 1000m. Can give this a shake. THAT'S A BEAUTY (10) filly by Lean Mean Machine from I'm Mary Too on debut. Sure to have come on following a recent trial. Monitor any market moves.
